Police in Kilgoris, Trans-Mara West are investigating an incident where an eight-year-old girl was allegedly killed by her father while he fought with her mother.  Area Deputy County Commissioner Hassan Noor said the girl was hit with a stick on the head and died on her way to the hospital.  "It was reported that the girl was killed by the father while trying to hit his wife following a domestic row. On realising the child had been injured, both parents rushed her to hospital but she did not make it," said Mr Noor.  He said the man and his wife were arrested and taken to Kilgoris Police Station. "The two are being interrogated and might be charged with murder.    Kilgoris couple arrested after baby dies during their fight   Police assaults woman in row over family car  Father from hell: Man throws baby into fire over quarrel with wife  Jailed mum contests ‘husband’ phone theft  Rich But Poor: Dispute delays family's access to property  Nyumba zimeteketezwa Trans-Mara  Kampuni ya sukari ya Transmara yafungwa By Kennedy Gachuhi | 5 hours ago By Pkemoi Ng’enoh and Denish Ochieng | 5 hours ago By Peter Ochieng  | 5 hours ago By Daniel Chege | 19 hours ago